    <note>Gong(2) Yuan [941] Yuanfu coalition. Zhang(1) Ruogu's [245] grandson-in-law. Yuan was the first Song Chuzhou, Suichang jinshi, whose last office was prefect of Bozhou, next door to Hezhou. He died before he could take another office and this probably accounts for his family remaining here, i.e. Hezhou, Liyang. He studied under Wang(2) Anshi [1762]. One grandson, Xiang [10188], moved to Suzhou. The rest of the family may have died with his other Grandson, Ji(2) [11558], who was killed by the Jin invaders at age 22. XCB, 484.21a, 501.8b. For jinshi date, see Zhejiang TZ, 123.30a. CBD, 5, 4499.</note>
